comments.comment:
My city has composting.  Most of my weekly garbages are non-recyclable plastic packaging. It drives me through the roof when business claim that the excessive package is what people are asking for!  Here's what I would ban ASAP:
- wrapping most fruits and vegetables, except the most fragile (raspberries);
- paper bags/boxes for the rest;
- plastic bags and bring your own; charge $1 per bag at the store (i.e. Switzerland);
- plastic packages for most stuff on sale;
- we have lots of wood in Canada so Gvt should legislate away from plastic packaging and into paper/cardboard packaging.  Even is spoiled by food, it can biodegrade in the garage;
- Most recyclable plastic containers are for us to feel better but are hard to reuse since not a lot of applications.
In conclusion, the Government needs to legislate hard ASAP since industry will never take a leadership role since they are not paying for the waste.
